author: cmpilato
msg: Propose r9045 for 1.0.2.

author: cmpilato
msg: Fix a bug which causes some cvs2svn-produced repositories to gain
spurious additional files when passed through a dump-load cycle.
Patch by: Max Bowsher <maxb@ukf.net>
* subversion/libsvn_fs/bdb/changes-table.c
(fold_change): The sequence "replace, delete" should fold to
"delete", not "no-op".

author: philip
msg: Follow up to r9033 (part of issue 1635).  Greg Hudson points out that
the subpool is not required.
* subversion/libsvn_ra_svn/editorp.c (ra_svn_handle_delete_entry): Use
the pool parameter rather than a subpool, it has an appropriate
lifetime.

author: kfogel
msg: Some book tweaks:
* doc/book/book/ch05.xml: Fix typo.
* doc/book/book/ch06.xml: Remove stuttered comma.
* doc/book/book/ch08.xml:
- Add missing word "to".
- Use the word "custom" instead of "proprietary" to describe the
ra_svn protocol, and modernize the description of Subversion's
use of WebDAV, both after consultation with Mike.
- In the "Effective Pool Usage" example, actually clear the pool
at the top of the loop, like the comment says, and destroy the
subpool immediately after the loop, which is what most of our
code does.
- Add slashes to the ends of some URLs.

author: kfogel
msg: * doc/book/book/ch05.xml: It's the users list, not the developers list.
